            "id": "51ad9cda4da94cda8230b",
            "questionText": "A city's water utility department is troubleshooting a problem with low water pressure in homes located on a hill compared to those in a valley. The main reservoir is located at a higher elevation. Homes in the valley are supplied with water from a point $!$50\\,\\text{m}$!$ vertically below the reservoir's water level, while homes on the hill receive water from a point $!$20\\,\\text{m}$!$ vertically below the reservoir's water level. Given that the density of water is $!$1000\\,\\text{kg/m}^3$!$ and the acceleration due to gravity is $!$9.8\\,\\text{m/s}^2$!$, calculate the pressure difference (in Pascals) between the water supply points for the valley homes and the hill homes.",
