            "id": "ab5adb624ffd4c9ab5f43",
            "questionText": "An automotive engineer is designing an off-road vehicle weighing $!$2400 \\text{ kg}$!$. The vehicle has four tires. Initially, it is equipped with standard tires, each having a contact area of $!$0.06 \\text{ m}^2$!$ with the ground; later, the tires are replaced with wide off-road tires, each having a contact area of $!$0.15 \\text{ m}^2$!$. Assuming the acceleration due to gravity is $!$9.8 \\text{ m/s}^2$!$, calculate the percentage reduction in the pressure exerted on the ground when using the wide off-road tires compared to the standard tires.",
